    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-08-13T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-08-13T10:00:00-05:00" n="433"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d433">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/9331: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-13T23:00:00+08:00"
                            >August 13, 1937—11 p.m. [<hi rend="italic">a.m.?</hi>]</date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 13—6 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>463. My August 12, 11 p.m. The area now held by outposts of police and volunteers
                    and American and British forces are those known as Sectors B, C and D in the
                    defence plan. Please note that Sector B includes West Hongkew area north of
                    Soochow Creek.</p>
                <pb facs="0400" n="393" xml:id="pg_393"/>
                <p>Chinese and Japanese reports indicate that a small clash occurred this morning
                    just north of North Station.</p>
                <p>In the vicinity of Nantao, Chinese have thrown boom across river consisting of
                    small steamers and junks, perhaps preparatory to sinking them and blocking
                    channel.</p>
                <p>Sent to the Department. Repeated to Peiping and Nanking.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
